meta {
  name: List Branch User Options
  type: http
  seq: 19
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/users/branch-users/options?page=1&limit=20
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:query {
  page: 1
  limit: 20
  ~search: raj
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

docs {
  Lightweight `{ id, name }` options listing **every active user** at the active
  branch, regardless of role — used by the Create-Order Radiology section's
  Technician picker (which must offer all branch staff, not only radiology
  technicians). The `id` is a `personId`.

  The active branch is resolved server-side from the JWT profile (never a body/query
  param, per CLAUDE.md §4.7); a request with no active branch returns 400
  `ACTIVE_BRANCH_REQUIRED`. `search` matches the person's first/last name
  (case-insensitive). Omit `page` for the full array; supply `page` for a
  `{ data, total, page, limit }` envelope.
}
